              <tr>
                <td bgcolor="" colspan="2" align="center"><b><font face="verdana" size="1" color="mintcream">T O P I C&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;R E V I E W</font></b></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td bgcolor="#37437B" valign="top" width="100" nowrap><font color="white" face="verdana" size="2"><b>Ghoulia_Ghostbuster</b></font></td>
                <td bgcolor="#37437B" valign="top" width="100%"><font color="white" face="verdana" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;01/11/2004&nbsp;: 11:08:11 PM</small><hr size="1"><span class="spnMessageText"> Graar's short guide to Crystalline golems in PoV<br /><br />Location: Plane of valor, rocky area.<br /><br />Recommended level: 63 (and embracing darkness)<br /><br />How to get there: Zone into PoV. You'll be at GY, invis, turn right and run untill you get to the river (this is near the razor-fiend camp btw). Follow the river untill you see a big building with two doors, open the door and head up the "stairs". Continue up the ledge untill you see golems. Neither the golems nor the spiders up there see invis, so feel free to explore.<br /><br />Now, head to the north-east corner, where you'll find a fairly open spot with room enough to aggro kite. I'm writing this from memory so can't tell you the exact coordinates, but you'll know when you see it. <br /><br />Preparation: Up on the zonewall should be far enough away from roamers for you to set up and buff. Get out pet, buff him and yourself up (shielding spell, manaskin and of course jboots/sow potions/run3).<br /><br />What mobs to pull: I've seen two mobs around this area: Golems and spiders. The spiders are immune to run-speed changing spells (root and snare), so you don't wanna mess with them. The golems are snareable and don't summon so these are obvious targets. A word of warning though, they run pretty fast, so grab a SoE from your friendly neighborhood druid or if you prefer, stick to jboots, which will also work although less safe.<br /><br />Suggested spell lineup:<br /><br />1) Embracing darkness (I only had dooming at the time, which gets resisted a bit more, but it's still possible)<br />2) Splurt<br />3) Dark plague<br />4) Pyro or FP if you have it<br />5) Saryns kiss<br />6) Pet buff/lich/buffs<br />7) Feign<br />8) Fear (lvl 4 version)<br /><br />How to kill: Two methods are useable. Root rot and aggro kite. I prefer aggro kiting, so that's what I'm going to write about. Root rotting is (as aggro kiting) pretty straight forward, so no explantion needed, although it's recommended you pull the mob to the ledge instead of rooting it on the spot because of wanderers.<br /><br />It's really simple, pull a golem with darkness, and aggro kite it using the above spells. I use lvl 4 fear to make sure pet never gets aggro. If darkness gets resisted, run away while hitting hotkey for darkness until you get the "out of range" message. Stop, recast darkness, proceed with aggro kiting. Stay near the zonewall, don't run near wanderes and you'll be just fine. <br /><br />Two final notes, always keep manaskin up and always keep pet hasted (obviously). Accidents will happen, and manaskin has saved my life life more than once :)<br /><br />Loot: Misc. vendorjunk which sells for up to 99pp. They are rumoured to drop ethereal parchments as well, but I have yet to see one drop.<br /><br />XP: Around 7-8pct AAxp per kill.<br /><br />Have fun, and safe hunting.</span></font></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td bgcolor="" colspan="2" align="center"><b><font face="verdana" size="1" color="mintcream">17&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;L A T E S T&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;R E P L I E S&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;(Newest First)</font></b></td>
